[54] p.
Printed for Thomas Cadman, At London : 1585.
In verse and prose. Running title reads: The Queenes Maiesties entertainment at Woodstocke. Includes "The tale of Hermetes", attributed to George Gascoigne, and a comedy which has been attributed to George Ferrers. Signatures: A-G⁴ (-G4, blank?). Imperfect: leaves A2-4 lacking. Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
